# =============================================================================
# NEVER COMMIT: model weights, checkpoints, datasets
# =============================================================================
# This is the most important section in this file, and it's first for a reason.
#
# Git stores every version of every file forever. A 500 MB checkpoint committed
# once stays in the history permanently, even if you `git rm` it in the next
# commit — every future `git clone` re-downloads it. Un-doing that requires
# rewriting history (git-filter-repo / BFG) and force-pushing, which breaks
# every existing clone.
#
# So: weights and datasets are LOCAL ONLY. They are reproducible (re-download
# the pretrained weights, re-run training) or they are your own source data —
# neither belongs in a code repository. Back them up separately if they matter.

# All runtime artifacts: uploaded images, downloaded weights, training runs.
# NOTE: .gitignore has no trailing-comment syntax — a `#` after a pattern on the
# same line becomes part of the pattern and silently matches nothing. Comments
# must sit on their own line. Verify rules with `git check-ignore -v <path>`
# rather than assuming.
storage/

# Model weight / checkpoint formats, wherever they land
*.pt
*.pth
*.onnx
*.safetensors
*.ckpt
*.bin
*.tflite
*.engine
*.pkl

# Framework output directories that appear wherever you run them from
runs/
wandb/
lightning_logs/
checkpoints/
outputs/

# HuggingFace / torch model caches, if ever pointed inside the repo
.cache/
hub/

# Datasets & annotations (COCO JSON can reach hundreds of MB)
datasets/
*.zip
*.tar
*.tar.gz


# =============================================================================
# Python
# =============================================================================
venv/
.venv/
env/
ENV/
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.so
.Python
build/
dist/
*.egg-info/
.eggs/

# Test / type-check caches
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.coverage
htmlcov/


# =============================================================================
# Database
# =============================================================================
# SQLite holds *your* project metadata — machine-local state, not source code.
# Committing it would mean merge conflicts on a binary file, which git cannot
# resolve. The schema lives in app/models/; the data stays on your machine.
*.db
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3
*.db-journal
*.db-wal
*.db-shm


# =============================================================================
# Node / frontend
# =============================================================================
node_modules/
dist/
dist-ssr/
.vite/
*.local

# Logs
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
pnpm-debug.log*


# =============================================================================
# Secrets & environment
# =============================================================================
# .env may hold API keys or absolute paths specific to your machine.
# .env.example IS committed — it documents which vars exist, with no values.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.pem
*.key


# =============================================================================
# Editors & OS
# =============================================================================
.vscode/
!.vscode/extensions.json
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini


# =============================================================================
# Test fixtures
# =============================================================================
# Sample images for trying things out stay local. If a fixture is genuinely tiny
# (a few KB) and needed for tests, un-ignore it explicitly with a `!` rule rather
# than loosening this one.
samples/
scratch/
